   DefaultBaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
   ImageSize->{432.85748291015625`, Automatic},
   ImageSizeRaw->{539., 221.},
   PlotRange->{{0, 539.}, {0, 221.}}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->
  "46a8a065-c400-43e2-8e98-07a458ad385f"],
 "\nYou job is to show that if ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", " ", ">", " ", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f478bea-252b-4d80-b6e9-41d77b89a56d"],
 " then ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["a", "2"], ">", "a"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bd0b84c5-7492-41b4-af7a-0dfe710eb1c9"],
 ".\n\n(a) Begin by stating what ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", ">", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dd45f4a4-dbb8-46a2-960e-bd9fed34f8ef"],
 " by definition means.\n\n\nThat is what you get to assume.\n\n(b) Also \
state what ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["a", "2"], ">", "a"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "445be0e8-84a5-4984-88b6-9fbe09be2db2"],
 " by definition means.\n\n\nThat is what you are trying to prove.\n\n(c) Use \
P10-P12 to prove (b) from (a). If you need to use it, you can assume 1 is in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["P", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "4f3c1cc5-80f2-4d66-8eb7-d6ed1e6985cf"],
 " without also proving that.\n\n\n"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7283836009935427`*^9, 3.728383602769161*^9}, {
