6e5d85e5afae"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To do this proof, the very first thing you do is write the definition of \
the limit out for the above two limits. Since the deltas in the two \
statements are not going to be the same, in the second statement call it ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "'"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "a32077f8-afe2-4254-b85d-06adca48a4c0"],
 " instead. The job is essentially to find the relationship between \[Delta] \
and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "'"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "eb58ccec-a63c-40fc-bfc4-f9a4bc07b8d5"],
 " that makes the two statements equivalent."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.828268854217546*^9, 3.8282689954176617`*^9}, {
  3.828269055481062*^9, 3.828269131081312*^9}, {3.828269507361368*^9, 
  3.82826950884654*^9}, {3.828272266113953*^9, 3.828272423582921*^9}, {
  3.828282449671196*^9, 3.828282455364807*^9}, {3.828283394115266*^9, 
  3.828283459756942*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"730b3663-a8fe-4f4f-88e6-\
0a2be38b96e7"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
